Description: Two joining fragments of low ring foot of pottery plate; light orange-brown clay with polished surface. Cut marks, perhaps from ancient use, on inside. Drilled for analysis.
Curator's comments: NAA by Hans Mommsen groups the piece with British Museum 1888,0601.728
Bibliographic references: Schlotzhauer & Villing 2006 / East Greek Pottery from Naukratis: The Current State of Research (p.56 Table 1)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GS.171)
